                " \n \nINTERNAL & EXTERNAL \n \nGENERAL MANAGER: NEW ROLLING STOCK FLEET RENEWAL PROGRAMME (NRSFRP) \nSALARY GROUP: Executive Management \nLOCATION: PRASA Corporate \nDEPARTMENT: Strategic Asset Development (SAD) \nPOST NUMBER: TBA \nREFERENCE: R&S/GMNRSFRP/SAD/273 \n \nDEPARTMENTAL MISSION: To lead and direct the planning, development, and implementation of PRASA\u2019s New Rolling Stock Fleet Renewal Programme.\n \nOUTPUTS:\n1. Contribute to the development and review of the SAD strategy and plans\n\u2022 Contribute to the Asset Development strategy and implementation plans in alignment and support of the Group strategy.\n\u2022 Lead and direct the development of the NRSFRP strategy and plans.\n\u2022 Review and align the NRSFRP strategy and plans with changing business needs or other developments.\n\u2022 Coordinate the implementation of the Design Review Process for additional train variants e.g., 25kV; Metro Express and Metro with Toilet variants.\n2. Oversee and direct the NRSFRP operations\n\u2022 Assume the role of PRASA Chief Representative on the Manufacturer and Supply Agreement (MSA) and Technical Support and Spares Supply Agreement (TSSSA) with the Gibela Rail Transport Consortium (RF).\n\u2022 Lead and direct the:\ndelivery and deployment of all new EMU train sets\nPAC (Provisional Acceptance Certificate) and FAC (Final Acceptance Certificate) processes including the development/review of the- Technical and Contractual documentation.\ntransfer of the Configuration Management documentation into the operational environment\nimplementation of Fleet Warranty Management and Maintenance Regime.\nIn-service Change and Configuration Management and sign off design change requests.\nfleet reliability growth as per TSSSA.\nthe PRASA Readiness (Preparation, Mobilization and Deployment) to support the local production.\nthe local production team for Mobilisation readiness in all quality Gate processes at the Local factory.\n\u2022 Oversee TSSSA and MSA:\nperformance management.\ncontract management.\npayments.\ntechnical training.\n3. Corporate governance, compliance, and risk management\n\u2022 Oversee the development and review of SOPs\n\u2022 Develop and manage the NRSFRP Risk Register\n\u2022 Review the Hazard Analysis for deployment corridors\n4. Management of Resources\n\u2022 Determine the Programmes priorities and ensure effective allocation of resources to these priorities.\n\u2022 Develop and implement efficiency measures to ensure optimum capacity utilisation and performance.\n\u2022 Manage human, physical, and financial resources in line with the organisational policies, processes, and procedures\n5. Management of stakeholder relationships\n\u2022 Build and maintain relationships with suppliers and internal customers.\n\u2022 Liaise with stakeholders i.e., Department of Transport, National Trea\n6. Reporting and advisory services\n\u2022 Provide advice in relation to NRSFRP operations.\n\u2022 Ensure general and management reporting on all NRSFRP matters\n \nKNOWLEDGE: \n\u2022 National Railway Safety Regulator Act (Act 16 of 2002, as amended)), National Railway Safety Permit Regulation, 2015, South African National Standard (SANS) 3000 series etc.\n\u2022 Contract Management\n\u2022 Business acumen\n\u2022 SCM, HCM, Finance management principles\n\u2022 Project management methodologies and principles\n \nSKILLS:\n\u2022 Leadership and management\n\u2022 Decision-making and problem-solving\n\u2022 Interpersonal\n\u2022 Communication and presentation\n\u2022 Conflict Management\n \nATTITUDES:\n\u2022 Resilient\n\u2022 Detail oriented\n\u2022 Deadline and results-oriented\n\u2022 Customer-centric\n \nCAPABILITIES:\nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS:\n\u2022 Degree in Engineering, Finance, Quantity Surveying, or equivalent\n\u2022 Preferably MBA or equivalent\n\u2022 Professional registration with an Engineering/ Project/Construction or Quantity Surveying professional body\n \nEXPERIENCE\n\u2022 10 years\u2019 project management/contracts management experience (leading and managing complex and multidisciplinary mega contracts/projects) in rolling stock.",
