                "ASSESSMENT SPECIALIST: MEDICAL PROGRAMME\nReference Number: SANAS/ASM/10\nClosing date:   25 Oct 2023\nPosition Type: Permanent\nLocation: Pretoria, Gauteng\n \nPurpose of the Job:\nSANAS seeks to employ an experienced Assessment Specialist with strong managerial and operational skills. As Assessment Specialist, the candidate is expected to conduct assessments and implement action plans from business unit objectives in conjunction with the Accreditation Manager.\n \nOverview:\nKEY PERFORMANCE AREAS:\n-Implement action plans from both business unit objectives.\n-Planning and conducting of assessments.\n-Manage assessment teams.\n-Confirm technical correctness of accreditation scopes during assessments.\n-Perform document reviews for new applications and check technical details of the application.\n-Contribute to assessment and financial planning with Accreditation Manager.\n-Participate in departmental projects objectives and deadlines.\n-Interact with various stakeholders and ensure that clients are provided with a satisfactory technical service.\n-Participate in public platforms e.g., conferences, assessor conclaves, stakeholder communication meetings. \n-Confirm all logistics pertaining to assessments that have been arranged by the administrators timeously i.e., accommodation, assessment packs, travel logistics, etc.\n \nCOMPULSORY REQUIREMENTS:\n-B Degree in a relevant technical qualification or equivalent qualification (e.g., Medical Technology, Bio-Medical Sciences).\n-Minimum of 5 years technical experience, of which 3 years must include accreditation experience.\n-Systems knowledge and practical experience in ISO 15189.\n-Knowledge of Accreditation Bodies requirements, i.e., ISO 17011 and ILAC/IAF requirements.\n-A valid driver\u2019s license (this role requires travelling).\n-Registration as a Technical Assessor for the relevant scheme is advantageous.\n \nCOMPETENCIES/KNOWLEDGE:\n-Ability to manage assessment teams under stressful conditions.\n-Ability to view the complete picture.\n-Good written and verbal communication\n-Delivering and meeting expectations\n-Computer literacy \u2013 MS Office\n-Planning, organising and good time management. \n-Adhering to principles and values\n-Analysing and attention to detail\n-Working with people and teamwork\n-Coping with pressure\n-Persuading and influencing\n-Technically inclined\n \nINDUSTRY\nGovernment, Public Sector, Parastatal",
                "PLEASE NOTE THE FOLLOWING:\nBy applying for this position and by submitting information to SANAS Career Services, irrespective as to how such information is submitted, you consent to the collection, collation, processing, and storing of such information and the use and disclosure of such information in accordance with THE POPI Act.\n \nThe South African National Accreditation Systems (SANAS), based in Pretoria, is listed as a Schedule 3A Public Entity according to the National Public Entities Classification. SANAS is mandated to be the Sole Provider of National Accreditation Services, whereby it formally recognises the technical competency of calibration and conformity assessment service providers that offer testing, inspection verification and calibration services as well as inspection against OECD GLP Principles in both the public and private domains.\n \nSalary: COMPETITIVE AND MARKET RELATED PACKAGE\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
