                " \nSOUTH AFRICAN NATIONAL ROADS AGENCY (SANRAL)\n ",
                "SENIOR TREASURY ACCOUNTANT\nNational\nPermanent     \n \nDescription\nPOSITION OBJECTIVE\nThe incumbent will compile treasury reports and analysis of treasury information including monitoring cash-flow, creating financial reports, verifying treasury figures, and preparing financial forecasts, all while ensuring adequate financial control and compliance with relevant legislation and reporting standards.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nA Bachelor\u2019s degree in accounting at an NQF level 8 or equivalent qualification.\nAt least five years\u2019 experience in the following:\nFinancial instruments: Loans and investment reporting\nPreparation of financial statements and financial reports in accordance with the International Finance Reporting Standards (IFRS).\nMust be a Chartered Accountant.\nExtensive knowledge and experience in the International Finance Reporting Standards (IFRS 7 and IFRS 9).\nKnowledge of SAP is essential.\n \nADVANTAGEOUS\nCaseWare\nExperience in the banking / financial services sector.\n \nTECHNICAL COMPETENCIES\nA detailed technical knowledge of the International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) and the implications for SANRAL treasury reporting requirements.\nKnowledge and understanding of the Public Finance Management Act (PFMA) and an understanding of the implications of treasury accounting within SANRAL.\nIn-depth knowledge of financial markets.",
                "KEY RESPONSIBILITIES\n \nTreasury Accounting and Reporting\nPerform and review reconciliations of Trial Balance to treasury system subledger.\nPerform, analyse and submit cash flow forecasts.\nPerform, analyse and submit funding requirements.\nReview and analyse notes to the financial statements relating to treasury.\n \nRegulatory reporting\nAnalyse and review Assets and Liability Committee (ALCO) reporting Model.\nPrepare, analyse and submit quarterly reports to Department of Transport.\nPrepare, analyse and submit quarterly reports to Audit and Risk Committee (ARC).\nPrepare, analyse and submit quarterly reports to National Treasury.\nReview, analyse and submit weekly borrowing reports to National Treasury.\n \nFinancial and Management Reporting\nPrepare, analyse and submit treasury reports to executive management and the Board.\nPrepare and submit IFRS-compliant annual financial statements, including notes, for financial instruments.\nDevelop treasury reports for roadshows.\nPrepare financial inputs to management and financial accountants as and when required.\nPrepare general statutory returns and reporting to regulatory authorities including monthly and quarterly reports to the Department of Transport and National Treasury. \n \nCompliance Management\nEnsure accounting and reporting adherence to IFRS, GRAPS, PFMA, JSE-listing requirements and related regulations.\nEnsure that reports are prepared accurately and timeously in accordance with statutory and regulatory requirements.\nFile and safeguard reports as per requirements.\nAssist with internal and external audit queries when necessary.\nPropose changes to policies and procedures relating to treasury accounting and reporting where necessary.\n \nhttps://career2.successfactors.eu/sfcareer/jobreqcareer?jobId=2274&company=southafr02\n \nCLOSING DATE: 26 OCTOBER 2023"
